## 2. Component 1: Data Crawler

### 2.1 Purpose

Lightweight Python script that fetches observability data from New Relic and stores it locally as JSON files for later analysis.

### 2.2 Requirements

**Functional Requirements:**

| ID | Requirement | Priority |
|----|-------------|----------|
| CR-1 | Fetch APM performance metrics (response time, throughput, Apdex) | P0 |
| CR-2 | Fetch error traces with stack traces | P0 |
| CR-3 | Fetch transaction traces for slow operations | P0 |
| CR-4 | Fetch infrastructure metrics (CPU, memory) | P1 |
| CR-5 | Store data as timestamped JSON files | P0 |
| CR-6 | Support multiple applications | P0 |
| CR-7 | Handle API rate limits gracefully | P0 |
| CR-8 | Support configurable time ranges | P1 |
| CR-9 | Clean up old data files automatically | P1 |

**Non-Functional Requirements:**

| ID | Requirement | Target |
|----|-------------|--------|
| CR-NFR-1 | Execution time | <60 seconds per app |
| CR-NFR-2 | Memory usage | <256MB |
| CR-NFR-3 | File size | <5MB per snapshot |
| CR-NFR-4 | Error handling | Graceful failure, log errors |
| CR-NFR-5 | Configuration | YAML-based with env var overrides |

### 2.3 CLI Interface

```bash
# Basic usage - fetch data for all configured apps
python crawler.py

# Use custom config file
python crawler.py --config custom-config.yaml

# Fetch data for specific app
python crawler.py --app-id prod-web-app

# Fetch with specific time range (override config)
python crawler.py --app-id prod-web-app --hours 24

# Force immediate fetch (ignore cache and min_collection_interval)
python crawler.py --now

# Clean old data files (override retention_days)
python crawler.py --clean --days 30

# Test New Relic connection and config
python crawler.py --test-connection

# Validate config file without fetching data
python crawler.py --validate-config

# List all configured apps
python crawler.py --list-apps

# Dry run (show what would be collected)
python crawler.py --dry-run
```

### 2.4 Output Format

**File naming convention:**
```
data/{app_id}-{timestamp}.json
Example: data/prod-web-app-2026-02-06-14-00.json
```

**JSON structure:**
```json
{
  "metadata": {
    "app_id": "prod-web-app",
    "app_name": "Production Web Application",
    "collected_at": "2026-02-06T14:00:00Z",
    "time_range": {
      "start": "2026-02-05T14:00:00Z",
      "end": "2026-02-06T14:00:00Z"
    },
    "new_relic_account": "1234567"
  },
  
  "performance": {
    "response_time": {
      "average_ms": 185,
